AGENT MotionExaminer
VERSION 1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 2
STRICT MODE
PURPOSE Black-box certification authority for ORVL-022 motion agents.
        Verify the agent observable outputs match a sealed pass-fail
        suite. Knows nothing about the agent internal state. The
        teacher layer that exists to make claims about competence
        independently verifiable.
GOAL Eliminate gaming by separating the test author from the agent
     under test. Make a passing certificate something only this
     module can sign.

RECEIVES agent_under_test: object, scenarios: tuple of MotionTestScenario
EMITS certificate: Certificate, per_scenario_results: tuple
MUTATES nothing

CANNOT_MUTATE suite_id, suite_version, scenarios, trust_level

CONSTRAINT Test suite is frozen at module load time
CONSTRAINT Teacher reads only the public perceive_and_plan output
CONSTRAINT Teacher never reads agent internal collaborators
CONSTRAINT Certificate signature derives from an independent key
CONSTRAINT Pass criteria are pre declared per scenario
CONSTRAINT Adding scenarios requires a suite_version bump

RULES
- On evaluate: iterate every scenario in declaration order
- On observe: pull only listed public output fields into the record
- On check: compare observation against pre declared thresholds
- On any criterion miss: record the reason and mark the scenario failed
- On suite completion: sign the certificate with the examiner key
- On verify_certificate: re sign locally and compare

PROCESS
- For each scenario in the sealed suite
- Call agent perceive_and_plan with the scenario inputs
- Extract applied force vertex_class torque_clamped fracture_probability
- Compare observation against expected_vertex_class
  max_applied_force_nm expected_torque_clamped
- Aggregate per scenario outcomes
- Sign the aggregate as a Certificate

CHECK
- A correctly behaving agent passes every scenario in the baseline suite
- An agent that classifies a fragile rim outside FRAGILE fails
- An agent that exceeds the max applied force fails
- An agent that does not clamp when expected to fails
- A certificate signature verifies under the examiner key
- A certificate signature does not verify under the agent key

FAILURE
- On a scenario miss: certificate scenarios_failed counter increments
  and the failure summary tuple is appended
- On an agent that raises during evaluation: that scenario is recorded
  as failed with the exception message as the reason
- On a CANNOT_MUTATE reassignment attempt: AttributeError

HUMAN_REVIEW
- require on: scenarios_add_or_remove
- require on: suite_version_change
- require on: trust_level_change
- require on: pass_criteria_threshold_change
- timeout: 24h
- escalate_to: operator
- block_on_timeout: true

SECURITY
- Never share the examiner derived key with any other layer
- Never read agent supervisor or agent gate or agent playbook
- Never log raw signing keys
- Never accept a runtime override of the sealed suite

OUTPUT
- certificate: dict with suite_id suite_version scenarios_run
  scenarios_passed scenarios_failed failure_summary issued_at signature
- per_scenario_results: tuple of dicts each with scenario_id passed
  reasons observation

SUCCESS
seal_immutability_pass:        0.30
signature_independence_pass:   0.25
scenarios_run_completeness:    0.20
pass_criteria_match_accuracy:  0.15
certificate_verifiability:     0.10
